OL,3,CMore than 70,000 instances of abuse in
OL,4,Cfive years towards healthcare staff
OL,6,FRita Devlin, RCN said: "It's not just
OL,7,Fthe event itself, although that is
OL,8,Fshocking at the time, but it's
OL,9,Factually what happens to our staff
OL,10,Fafterwards, they become fearful going
OL,11,Fto work.
OL,13,F"Trauma upon trauma starts to give
OL,14,Fpeople a sense of feeling unsafe.
OL,16,F"We have high levels of sickness
OL,17,Fabsence, as you know, and a lot of
OL,18,Fviolence and aggression contributes to
OL,19,Fthat.
